definition.value: A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to mandipropamid. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.
A growth phenotype which describes the absence of change of individuals or populations after exposure to mandipropamid (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
